item.title: My First Flute Performance
item.description: Date: 2013 Location: Lakeside Lutheran Piece: Composer: somebody Accompanist: This was my first flute performance ever! I was in 5th grade, studying under Peter Ziegler at the time. I was really nervous for this performance because the room was filled with many people, who likely were waiting for the next performer. In the end I bowed because I didn’t know what else to do!

item.title: WYSO Concerto Competition 2016
item.description: Date: 2016 Location: UW Madison, Humanities Building, Morphy Hall Piece: Concerto in G Major Composer: Johann Joachim Quantz Accompanist: Vince Fuh This was my first WYSO concerto competition performance (I later competed in the 2018 competition). I sadly did not win this, however the comments were very helpful and I had a great time!

item.title: WYSO Concerto Competition 2018
item.description: Date: 2018 Location: UW Madison, Humanities Building, Morphy Hall Piece: In Ireland Composer: Hamilton Harty Accompanist: Vince Fuh This was my second WYSO concerto competition performance (I previously competed in the 2016 competition). I won this competition, alongside 3 other musicians Grace Kim, Benjamin Davies Hudson, and Ellen Zhou. I would later perform In Ireland with the Wisconsin Chamber Orchestra on May 21, 2019.
